\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces S1-lure rates (\%) on conflict items by model and category. Bolded numbers indicate vulnerable categories (lure rate $>$10\%). OLMo columns provide cross-architecture replication from an independent model family. Loss aversion is vulnerable in OLMo Instruct (33\%) but immune in Llama (0\%); availability shows a Llama-specific vulnerability (13\%) absent in all other models. Natural frequency base rate framing increases lure rates (Llama: $84\% \to 100\%$; R1-Distill: $4\% \to 40\%$). --- = not yet evaluated on the expanded set.}}{4}{table.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:behavioral}{{1}{4}{S1-lure rates (\%) on conflict items by model and category. Bolded numbers indicate vulnerable categories (lure rate $>$10\%). OLMo columns provide cross-architecture replication from an independent model family. Loss aversion is vulnerable in OLMo Instruct (33\%) but immune in Llama (0\%); availability shows a Llama-specific vulnerability (13\%) absent in all other models. Natural frequency base rate framing increases lure rates (Llama: $84\% \to 100\%$; R1-Distill: $4\% \to 40\%$). --- = not yet evaluated on the expanded set}{table.1}{}}
